I have the honor of working on behalf of Arizonans in the seat once held by the late Senator John McCain. His commitment to putting Arizonans ahead of partisan politics has guided my own service, and it will continue to guide me over these next six years.

I’ve met many Arizonans in every corner of our state who've shared with me stories of hope for a better future. Every day, these stories drive my work here in the Senate and I’m proud to continue breaking through partisan gridlock to pass laws that will improve their lives.

2022 has been a tough year for a lot of folks, but also shown the spirit and resolve of Arizonans. I’m grateful to continue representing our state in the Senate and work just as hard for you as you do for your loved ones. To you and your family - Happy New Year, Arizona!
